dsgrovehuntingguide.showMessage?topicID=3182.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.showMessage?topicID=3165.topic"> Next Topic >> </a> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top  class=headings><font color=#333399>Author</font></td><td valign=top  class=headings><font color=#333399>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/userberus00.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Serberus00</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/26/01 6:30:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Eastern Wastes Quad Kiting Problem</span><hr size=1> In eastern wastes whenever I try to quad kite anything when it gets low on health it will stop moving.<br>
<br>
This doesn't seem to happen anywhere else but in eastern wastes.<br>
<br>
I've hunted the snow cougars and dire wolves in iceclad ocean and they always stay in a pack until they are dead, but in eastern wastes, the dire wolves, rhinos and manticores all seperate when they get low on health.<br>
<br>
I assume i'm not the only one whose had this problem? (particularly as its happened with two characters)<br>
Are there any mobs in EW that don't behave like this?<br>
<br>
Thanks<br>
<br>
Serberus <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukayleigh88.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kayleigh88</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/26/01 7:25:33 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://communities.msn.ca/_Secure/0MAAAAAQRZJwobQ10JEgBEVnTf2fwE2ks75hF4L27KUCO9em3zq3LL6!q8Jf7rFgS2dffE3vlh*IEAAAAWBMRAw/kayleigh.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Eastern Wastes Quad Kiting Problem</span><hr size=1> General rule for quadding is that you need to pick mobs that are socialable to each other. This usually means that they will assist each other when attacked. For quad kiting purposes, it means that they will not run away as quickly when low on health.<br>
<br>
I have personally tried the mammoths and rhinos in EW and they are definately bad targets for quad kite. They run in different directions when low on health.<br>
<br>
Kayleigh, level 54 druid, Tholuxe Paells <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uknightward.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KnightWard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/26/01 2:37:47 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Eastern Wastes Quad Kiting Problem</span><hr size=1> If it stops moving completly, its your snare holding them in place.<br>
<br>
-Fen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udaktariplainsrunner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daktari Plainsrunner</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home1.gte.net/chiefq/icon1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/28/01 12:49:03 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home1.gte.net/chiefq/cop.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Eastern Wastes Quad Kiting Problem</span><hr size=1> They seperate because they have different amounts of hit points.  Once they are low enough on hit points (in flee mode) they will stop.  The different animals stop at different points because they reach their &quot;snare flee mode&quot; at different levels.<br>
<br>
As mentioned, kite similar mobs to prevent this.  If a mob is with a like mob it wont stop attacking until it is the only one left and its in flee mode.<br>
 <p><img src=http://home1.gte.net/chiefq/signamesmall.gif></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uknightward.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KnightWard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/28/01 1:21:25 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Eastern Wastes Quad Kiting Problem</span><hr size=1> The best example is Wurlas and Ulthoks.<br>
<br>
-Fen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uguildzero.showPublicProfile?language=EN>guildzero</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/29/01 9:59:25 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Eastern Wastes Quad Kiting Problem</span><hr size=1> It gets worse... At higher levels they can pop back to their original locations... <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.showMessage?topicID=3182.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.showMessage?topicID=3165.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.emailToFriend?topicID=3190.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.threadControl?topicID=3190.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3190.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3190.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><